Package: sniffer-ebpf
Version: 0.83.0-1
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Alonso <alonsoir@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: 791
Depends: libbpf1 (>= 1:1.0), libc6 (>= 2.34), libgcc-s1 (>= 3.3.1), libjsoncpp25 (>= 1.9.5), liblz4-1 (>= 1.9), libprotobuf32 (>= 3.21.12), libstdc++6 (>= 11), libzmq5 (>= 4.3), libzstd1 (>= 1.5.2), libprotobuf-c1 (>= 1.4)
Section: net
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/alonsoir/test-zeromq-c-
Description: eBPF-based network packet sniffer with ML features
 High-performance packet sniffer using eBPF/XDP technology that
 captures 83 network features per packet for machine learning analysis.
 .
 Features:
  - Kernel-level packet capture with eBPF
  - 83 network features extraction (TCP flags, ports, sizes, etc.)
  - Dynamic batch processing with configurable windows
  - Protobuf serialization with LZ4 compression
  - ZMQ distributed pipeline for real-time processing
  - Systemd integration for automatic startup
 .
 This package is designed for network monitoring, anomaly detection,
 and machine learning model training on network traffic.
